      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Power of Green</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Yes, government can impose new carbon and gasoline taxes to raise the price of energy and to reduce fuel consumption. It will be an inconvenience for the rich but a tragedy for the poor. Wealthy families may decide to live with one S.U.V. instead of three. However, on the far side of town, many families will sink deeper into debt as they try to pay for heat and light and for basic transportation in an automobile-dominated culture.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Yes, government can impose new carbon and gasoline taxes to raise the price of energy and to reduce fuel consumption. It will be an inconvenience for the rich but a tragedy for the poor. Wealthy families may decide to live with one S.U.V. instead of three. However, on the far side of town, many families will sink deeper into debt as they try to pay for heat and light and for basic transportation in an automobile-dominated culture.</p>
        <p>Who speaks for environmental justice in America in the new conversations about global warming and national energy policy?  Rev. Robert Francis Murphy  Falmouth, Mass.</p>
      </block>
